SIMPLE: embase
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embase
<hw>Em*base"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>em-</ets> + <ets>base</ets>, a. or v. t.: cf. OF.
<ets>embaissier</ets>.]</ety> <def>To bring down or lower, as in
position, value, etc.; to debase; to degrade; to deteriorate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Embased</qex> the valleys, and embossed the hills.</q>
<rj><qau>Sylvester.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Alloy in coin of gold . . . may make the metal work the better,
but it <qex>embaseth</qex> it.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such pitiful embellishments of speech as serve for nothing but to
<qex>embase</qex> divinity.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embasement</ent>⟦br⟧
